The paper deals with developing a model for task-expert matching systems, which involves online platforms and human experts. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of feedback obtained from past matches, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The problem of efficient utilization of experts is a social issue, which can be addressed using social network analysis (cs.SI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
